          <div class="font-normal text-md sm:text-lg md:text-xl lg:text-2xl">
            <p>More than half of Indonesia&#8217;s climate change emissions are related to deforestation, peatland degradation and fires, and must be addressed to meet its Paris Agreement targets. In more than two decades in Indonesia, we have worked to reveal the extent of peatland emissions and degradation, show that restoration is possible and cost effective for mitigation and also helps with adaptation, while supporting healthy and prosperous communities and biodiversity.</p>
